(Figs. 11 - 12)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageNumber="6">Holotype: worker, Suriname, Nieuw Amsterdam, 30.3.1996, coll. D. Makhan (only the holotype).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="6">Description (holotype worker): Length 1.8 mm. Colour yellow-brown. Total head length 0.7 mm, width 0.45 mm, with spatulate hairs. mandible length 0.25 mm, large, inner teeth absent and with thick hairs. Eyes large. Antennae yellow-brown, scape with spatulate hairs. Mesosoma length 0.5 mm, width 0.3 mm, with spatulate hairs. Petiole with 0.1 mm, postpetiole width 0.15 mm, with spatulate hairs. Spongiform appendages absent. Gaster length 0.5 mm, width 0.4 mm, with spatulate hairs.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="6">Etymology: This species is named after my son Rishwan Makhan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
